# what is a computer?

is an electronic device that processes data and provides input and output to users.

the computer can be used for writing documents, sending e-mails, surfing the Internet, playing games, etc.

A computer is made up of two components :

# hardware

is any part of a computer that has a physical structure
Hardware consists of two components:
### input 
- keyboard = teclado
- mouse = ratón 
- microphone = micrófono
- usb = memoria
- scanner = escaner 

 ### output devices
- heardphones = audifonos de cabeza
- monitor = pantalla
- speaker = bocina
- printer = impresora


# computer hardware

- monitor = monitor
- case = caja
- motherboard = placa de base
- CPU = unidad central de procesamiento o procesador
- main memory RAM = memoria principal RAM
- expansion cards = trajetas de expansión (videos y graficos)
- power supply unit = fuente de alimentación
- optical disk drive = unidad de disco óptico
- hard disk drive = unidad de disco duro
- keyboard = teclado
- mouse = ratón

# sotfware

is any set of instructions that tells the hardware what to do

is any set of instructions that tells the hardware what to
do It control how the computer works. 

### browers
- internet explorer
- mozilla firefox
- google chrome
### games
- solitarie
### oficce
- word
- excel
- powerpoint
### all programs
anything listed under all programs and anything you download

# glosario

- device (divais) = dispositivo, aparato, equipo.
- input = entrada, aportacion, aporte, ingreso.
- output = salida, produccion, resultado.
- provides (provaids) = provee, proporciona, facilita, ofrece.
- storage = almacenamiento, almacen, memoria, deposito.
- retrieval (retreivol) = recuperacion, recuperar, rescate, restablesimiento.
- send (tsend) = eniar, mandar, transmitir, hacer llegar, remitir.
- browse = navegar, explorar, consultar, visitar.
- handle = manejar, atender, manipular, controlar, manija.
- spreadsheets (esprechis) = hojas de calculo, planillas.
- hard = duro, fuerte.
- soft = suave, blando.
- physical (fisical) = fisico, corporal, anatomico.
- tells = fisica.
- key = tecla, llave.
- item = articulo, objeto, punto.



